items.title: Problems with importing dataset from scikit-learn
items.body:
I try to run the attached code and the attached error pops up. I try to run the code through pycharm and scikit learn and tensorflow are installed.

I tried to perform python setup.py install as the comment suggests, in the path of

C: \ Users \ nirkov \ AppData \ Roaming \ Python \ Python36 \ site-packages \ sklearn \ __ check_build

And that did not solve the problem. Am I wrong where I execute the command?

Does anyone know what the problem might be? (I was looking for this problem on the web, but unfortunately I could not fix the problem)

the code - 

import numpy as np
import tensorflow as tf
from sklearn.datasets import fetch_california_housing

housing = fetch_california_housing()
m, n = housing.data.shape
housing_data_plus_bias =  np.c_[np.ones((m,1)),housing.data]

X = tf.constant(housing_data_plus_bias, dtype=tf.float32, name="X")
Y = tf.constant(housing.target.reshape(-1,1), dtype=tf.float32, name="Y")
X_Transpose = tf.transpose(X)
theta = tf.matmul(tf.matmul(tf.matrix_inverse(tf.matmul(X_Transpose, X)), X_Transpose), y)

with tf.Session() as sess:
    theta_value = theta.eval()
